Guard WorldObject::MovePositionToFirstCollision against invalid source coords.

A bot resuming a long-unloaded BG instance (e.g. Warsong Gulch) can carry a
stale Position whose x/y are outside MAP_HALFSIZE. Without this guard,
GetHitPosition() below underflows the grid-cell index inside the vmap tile
lookup and dereferences NULL, crashing the world server.

Incident reference: May 2026 cmangos-classic outage in this homelab. gdb on
the captured core showed SIGSEGV at MovePositionToFirstCollision+1424 with
RAX=0, immediately after a "Map::MessageBroadcast: Player ... have invalid
coordinates X:-18504 Y:-10635 grid cell [4294967253:192]" log line (grid
index = UINT32_MAX - 42, classic underflow).

The runtime DB fix (relocate stuck characters to their homebind, clear
character_battleground_data) stopped the bleeding but did not address the
underlying NULL deref. This patch adds the input validation that the rest
of the codebase already assumes (cf. WorldObject::IsPositionValid which
uses the same MaNGOS::IsValidMapCoord helper).

--- a/src/game/Entities/Object.cpp
+++ b/src/game/Entities/Object.cpp
@@ -1655,6 +1655,18 @@

 void WorldObject::MovePositionToFirstCollision(Position& pos, float dist, float angle)
 {
+    // Guard against callers passing invalid source coords. Stale Position
+    // state on a bot resuming a long-unloaded BG instance lets the
+    // GetHitPosition call below underflow the grid-cell index inside the
+    // vmap tile lookup, dereferencing NULL and crashing the world server.
+    // Incident: May 2026, RAX=0 at MovePositionToFirstCollision+1424.
+    if (!MaNGOS::IsValidMapCoord(pos.x, pos.y, pos.z))
+    {
+        sLog.outError("MovePositionToFirstCollision: invalid src (%.2f, %.2f, %.2f) for %s; skipping",
+                      pos.x, pos.y, pos.z, GetGuidStr().c_str());
+        return;
+    }
+
     float destX = pos.x + dist * cos(angle);
     float destY = pos.y + dist * sin(angle);
     float destZ = pos.z;
